This paper deals with the problem of domain adaptation in computer vision, specifically for object detection in urban driving scenes. The paper proposes a learned augmentation network to transfer specific sensor effects from a real dataset to a synthetic dataset, which is a common technique in computer vision and falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also involves deep learning techniques, which suggests it could fall under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The problem of domain adaptation is also relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and graphics (cs.GR) communities, as it involves transferring knowledge from one domain to another.
